   "source": [
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import fem\n",
    "print 'number of threads: %i' % (fem.fortran_module.fortran_module.num_threads(),)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "n = 10\n",
    "w = fem.continuous.model_parameters(n)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f49d06accd0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(8,4))\n",
    "ax[0].matshow(w)\n",
    "w_flat = w.flatten()\n",
    "hist = ax[1].hist(w_flat, ec='k', alpha=0.5)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = fem.continuous.time_series(w, l=1e4)"
   ]

   "source": [
    "tab = []\n",
    "for i in range(n):\n",
    "    tab.append([x[i].min(), x[i].max(), x[i].mean()])\n",
    "pd.DataFrame(data=tab, columns=['min', 'max', 'average'], index=1+np.arange(n))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {

     "output_type": "display_data"

   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(n, 1, figsize=(16, 4))\n",
    "for i in range(n):\n",
    "    ax[i].plot(x[i, :500], 'k-')\n",
    "    ax[i].axis('off')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "model = fem.continuous.model()\n",
    "x1, x2 = x[:,:-1], x[:,1:]\n",
    "model.fit(x1, x2, iters=10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f499208fb50>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(4,4))\n",
    "ax = plt.gca()\n",
    "w_fit_flat = model.w.flatten()\n",
    "ax.scatter(w_flat, w_fit_flat, c='k')\n",
    "grid = np.linspace(w.min(), w.max())\n",
    "ax.plot(grid, grid, 'b--')\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel('true parameters')\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel('inferred parameters')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x2_prediction = model.predict(x1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.figure.Figure at 0x7f498f859cd0>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, ax = plt.subplots(n, 1, figsize=(16, 4))\n",
    "for i in range(n):\n",
    "    ax[i].plot(x2[i, :500], 'k-')\n",
    "    ax[i].plot(x2_prediction[i, :500], 'r-')\n",
    "    ax[i].axis('off')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
